"{\"uid\": \"catholicnewsagency.com-news-258565-stunning-upset-cole-hocker-s-catholic-high-school-cheers-as-he-breaks-olympic-record\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByDaniel Payne  CNA Staff, Aug 7, 2024 /             13:21 pm  A stunning surprise victory at the Paris Olympics on Tuesday left spectators at an Indianapolis Catholic school cheering as a former student broke a major Olympic record and brought home a gold medal for the United States.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 19, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\", \"score\": 0.9920525080754562, \"rank\": 0.0042235108663011885, \"text\": \"CNA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\"}, {\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999222682014757, \"rank\": 7.565506662286436e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indianapolis native Cole Hocker astounded the sporting world on Tuesday when he clinched a last-minute win in the men's 1,500-meter race at the Paris 2024 Olympics, pulling down the gold and setting a new Olympic record of 3:27.65.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9962366371773703, \"rank\": 0.0035763151983064885, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC News referred to the victory as a \\\"stunning upset\\\" as Hocker pulled past world champion Josh Kerr in the final seconds of the race, crossing the finish line with his arms outstretched.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\", \"score\": 0.751379680103922, \"rank\": 0.32967299001996236, \"text\": \"NBC News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 612, \"end\": 616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9993769930205161, \"rank\": 0.000622881411256692, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hocker was still in third place with roughly 10 seconds left in the race before a final sprint put him just inches ahead of Kerr to take the top spot.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WOW.\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_of_Wrestling\", \"score\": 0.6036579103894314, \"rank\": 0.6075354413115076, \"text\": \"WOW\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_of_Wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_of_Wrestling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\ude31A STUNNING upset in the men's 1500m as AMERICAN COLE HOCKER takes gold!#ParisOlympicspic.twitter.com/wlq81lbvSO  In his hometown, meanwhile, a crowd at his alma mater Cathedral High School in Indianapolis watched and cheered as Hocker pulled off the incredible win.\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"COLE HOCKER\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedi